For almost 10 years, I've been with him on the road more than I've seen my family. I was there on his first day in FCW. I remember I told Amanda, Don't worry, he will kick out, he's Brodie. description: Music...Crash Cove by Josh Mancell, Mutato Muzika, Mark Mothersbaugh (Crash Team Racing)https://youtu.be/DuySka03D3kUse the Ice Kunai on the Fox's Fire A by Goemon Production Team (Mystical Ninja: Starring Goemon)https://youtu.be/_eIj2RYLgX0Friendly Neighbors by Akio Ohmori, Ritsuo Kamimura, Keiichi Suzuki, Hirokazu Tanaka (Earthbound)https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XBB5zxjZfhw&ab_channel=splatMeggyThanks To...Keith Apicary/Nathan Barnatt for the intro from PWG All Star Weekend 11https://twitter.com/keithapicaryBrian Nguyen's Harper story can be read here (the actual event happened at a house show, sorry)https://twitter.com/WWE_RefBrian/status/1343336415170502656Belen for the Thunderdome Sasha footagehttps://twitter.com/Belents13AHROOMEE for the Dragon gate cliphttps://twitter.com/AHROOMEE/status/1299166095027257344WHANG for the wonderful book-readinghttps://twitter.com/JustinWhangthatretro for the Are You Afraid Of orton endinghttps://twitter.com/ThatRetrolance madewell for Mrs. Doubtfire endinghttps://twitter.com/TrulyMADEWELLcharles chase for the Simpsons endinghttps://twitter.com/IAmCharlesChaseHeisenb3rg for the Kane balloon endingA Mob Of Duckshttps://twitter.com/AMobOfDucksMattyid for Cyberdick 2077https://twitter.com/MattyIDSteve Williams/aeonlinear for the typical Simpsons greatnesshttps://www.youtube.com/user/aeonlinearNotes...I'm always cautious about including any tribute to a wrestler because Botchamania is seen as an important thing to some and direspectful to others, but hopefully regardless of your viewpoint you'll understand there's nothing but love intended here. I've made more of an attempt to mix up the WWE clips with other companies to avoid those pesky copyright issues which are more likely to pop up when the clips are together.I love WHANG's work and was flattered he responded positively to my DM when he could have easily told me to piss off.The site is back-up but uhhhh it's reverted back to 2016 for some reason. It's being worked on though so fingers crossed.Until then, it's no secret 2020 has been fucking shit but I have to admit that making Botchamania has been one of the anchors to keep me sane during all this and I hope in some small way it's helped whoever is reading this.List Of Companies And Where To Find Them...WWE Network to watch Timothy Thatcher bust his cauliflower earhttps://www.wwe.com/wwenetworkAEW Dynamite for paper-throwinghttps://www.allelitewrestling.comAAA's Official YouTube got removed (and no-one knows why right now) but Triplemania can be found herehttps://youtu.be/FA7g12Cmcy8The Taz Show (aka AEW Dark) can be found herehttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCFN4JkGP_bVhAdBsoV9xftA83 Weeks can be subbed herehttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCCqQc7Pa1u4plPXq-d1pHqQDragon Gate's YouTube channel is herehttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCekKOhczmszWjqBFLvdFy4AICW: NHB still has a twitterhttps://twitter.com/ICWNHBThat's your lot, here's your usual social media links and keep yourself safe until next videohttps://twitter.com/Maffewgregghttps://www.facebook.com/botchamania/

description: Stefan Thomas invested in the digital currency Bitcoin in 2011, back when it sold for just $2. Today, it sells for $35,000 per bitcoin, leaving Thomas with a $225 million fortune. The only problem — he can’t remember the password to access his digital wallet. Ten years ago, when he bought the bitcoins, he misplaced the password. Now he has used 8 of his 10 login attempts before the account locks him out of his treasure forever.

title: Rugby Player Reacts to VON MILLER (Denver Broncos LB) #26 The NFL Top 100 Players of 2020!
tags: [none]
description: Sup everyone and welcome back to another Rugby Player Reacts reaction video!My name is Jacob McDonald and I am a New Zealand born rugby player that has fallen in love with the great game of American Football. What I haven't done is turn my back on my own sport and it's my goal to bridge the two as much as I can through videos like this.This sport is straight up fun. I've enjoyed every minute of discovering the world of American Football and it's rich history and for the past almost 3 years I have been bringing that journey of discovery to my YouTube channel, in it's entirety.In this particular series of videos I have given my unbiased, unfiltered reaction to each and every one of The Top 100 NFL Players of 2020 and their individual player videos that are released each and every year on The NFL YouTube channel. This is the 3rd year in a row that I've done this series and I can see it becoming an annual thing no doubt.In this video I take a look at VON MILLER who is an NFL LINEBACKER that plays for THE DENVER BRONCOS!He was officially voted by his fellow NFL peers as Number 26 on The Top 100 NFL Players of 2020 list. Last year he featured at Number 10 on the list.You can find the original video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PJo2XhqfIJk&list=PLRdw3IjKY2gk7bnzZHoqOu0kdnG96s5Di&index=75At the end of the day I am a fan of sport. A huge fan. I am a fan of athletic ability. Raw talent. I am a fan of moments in sport that make the hair stand up on your neck.. (mine are right now) I love seeing bonds made between Fathers, Sons, Mothers, Daughters, Coaches, Players etc. I love seeing juke moves that make your jaw drop, blistering out-and-out speed, crunching blocks, runs and tackles that make you cringe. I love it all. It's only now having watched the sport for almost 3 years that these plays mean more than just the impact you see. I can start to notice the parts of the game that get missed in the lead up to a big play like that and that makes the game so much better.I'm not saying I know everything. I never will! And neither will you lol.. But man this journey has been a fun one so far and I hope it never ends!There was a reason I was meant to search up YouTube that fateful day and embark on this mission to bridge the two epic sports so that we can enjoy both, just like I do.The story goes, on a fateful day back in May of 2018 I decided to bring up YouTube and search for exactly what the title of this video says. I wanted to find a rugby player out there that had taken an unbiased interest in American Football and could then give me some of their thoughts on the game and what the differences were.To my surprise, that video did not exist ANYWHERE!It was at that moment I decided to take it upon myself to be that person. I was going to be that rugby player that decided at 27 years of age to switch sports and dive DEEP into learning all I could about this new exciting sport.I remember it well. I download my first screen recorder, turned on my camera, picked up my balls and went about creating my very first Rugby Player Reacts to NFL reaction video.That was in May of 2018 and I simply have no stopped since. I always expected to get bored eventually. However, I can safely say that as I continue to watch more and more and the intricacies of the game become a little more clearer I am actually enjoying the game as much as I ever have and that is exciting!I want to officially welcome you to this YouTube video series Rugby Player Reacts to The Top 100 NFL Players of 2020 and I hope you had fun, I hope you enjoyed the video and I hope you enjoy the next one and the next one after that!My YouTube channel will never be pigeon-holed into one niche regardless of what the YouTube algorithm tells me. Reaction videos are just a part of what I create and the content I bring to this channel so please by all means check out some more of my video playlists and I hope you stick around!Much love and peace out!Jake.BECOME A CHANNEL LEGEND:https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCfjFBgHkjKkzkQm92dzfvrw/joinFOLLOW JACOB MCDONALD:https://linktr.ee/jacobmcdonaldFOLLOW MAJOR KEY PHYSIQUES:https://linktr.ee/majorkeyphysiquesFOLLOW JAKE'S WIDE WORLD OF SPORTS:https://linktr.ee/jakeswwosPLEDGE YOUR SUPPORT:https://www.patreon.com/jacobmcdonald27
